title: Attack Force Z 1981 (Action Movie) Mel Gibson blasting his way to hell and back!

sources.title: Attack Force Z 1981 (Action Movie) Mel Gibson blasting his way to hell and back!
sources.description:
Mission impossible, heroes unstoppable.
During World War II, a special operations team of Australian commandos known as Attack Force Z is deployed to a remote Pacific island on a daring mission to extract key survivors and gather vital intelligence. Amidst the perilous jungle and enemy forces, the commandos must rely on their wits and training to succeed against overwhelming odds.

Original title: Attack Force Z (1981)
Dubbed audio & subtitles available in many languages.


Director: Tim Burstall
Script: Roger Marshall
Cast: John Phillip Law, Mel Gibson, Sam Neill, Chris Haywood, Sylvia Chang, John Waters
Genres  Action, Drama, History, War


00:00 – Full Movie with subtitles
01:15 – 15 January 1945: Captain Kelly briefs his team on the mission to rescue plane crash survivors on a Japanese-occupied island.
12:45 – Lieutenant Veitch eliminates a Japanese sentry, securing a safe path for the squad's advance.
25:30 – Sergeant Costello discovers a hidden cache of enemy weapons, altering their strategic approach.
38:15 – Able Seaman Bird engages in a tense standoff with Japanese soldiers, showcasing his combat prowess.
51:00 – The team encounters local resistance fighters, forging an alliance to navigate the hostile territory.
1:03:45 – Captain Kelly confronts a moral dilemma after uncovering sensitive information from a captured enemy officer.
1:16:30 – The squad initiates a daring extraction under heavy fire, culminating in a critical decision that impacts their mission's outcome.
